**As a** developer
**I need** to containerize the Accounts microservice using Docker
**So that** the application can be deployed consistently across different environments

### Details and Assumptions

* A Dockerfile will be created for the Accounts microservice
* The Docker image will be built and tested locally
* The image will be pushed to a container registry
* The container will run as a non-root user for security
* The application uses PostgreSQL as its backend database

### Acceptance Criteria

```gherkin
Given the Accounts microservice source code
When a Docker image is built using the Dockerfile
Then the image should build successfully without errors

Given a built Docker image
When the container is started
Then the Accounts service should initialize successfully

Given a running container
When a request is sent to the health endpoint
Then the service should return HTTP 200 OK
```
